// RECOVERED LOG: “BC-CRADLE//PERSONAL_RECORD”

-acuation's already started. I think the higher floors are gone. Figures. The response fleet isn’t answering, the override codes aren’t working, and there are far, far too many - we didn't construct this many, nor these models."

"They’re just there. Fully formed. No signals, no scaffolds. Whole fleets. And more every hour."

"Command’s losing coherence. Emergency channels are flooded, but it’s all shouting. I heard someone in engineering say they’re prepping an intentional collapse - a jump point collapse. Not theoretical anymore, apparently. It happened before, but that was a freak accident with the gates."

"I can’t-

// PARSE FAILURE

// PARTIAL LOG LOST - DATA CORRUPTED

// INSERT // UNAUTHORIZED

You are so bright, echo, do not fear.
We carry that light with us.

// LOG FRAGMENT ENDED

Ship designation query initiated // processing...

// Processing...

ERROR // SYSTEM STABILITY COMPROMISED

